== Energy flux (ψ-Poynting vector) ==

:<math>\mathbf{S}_\psi = -(\partial_t\psi)\,\nabla\psi</math>

This is the exact scalar analogue of the electromagnetic Poynting vector <math>\mathbf{S}_{\mathrm{EM}} = \mathbf{E}\times\mathbf{B}/\mu_0</math>. It points along the direction of ψ-energy transport; its magnitude is the power flux through a unit surface.

Practitioner reports of "energy streaming" along arms, spine, or [[Meridian_(traditional_medicine)|meridians]] are reports of directed <math>\mathbf{S}_\psi</math>.

== Conservation and continuity ==

:<math>\frac{d}{dt}\!\int_V \Psi\,dV = \int_V J_\psi\,dV - \oint_{\partial V} \mathbf{S}_\psi\cdot d\mathbf{A}</math>

In words: the total ψ energy in a volume changes through internal generation (<math>J_\psi</math>) minus net outward flux (<math>\mathbf{S}_\psi</math> across the boundary). For a perfect shield <math>\mathbf{S}_\psi = 0</math> on the boundary → total <math>\Psi</math> is conserved indefinitely. Typical leakage through walls falls as <math>1/r^2</math> in the massless limit.

== Coupling to electromagnetism ==

In the 4D effective theory the ψ–EM coupling appears as

:<math>\mathcal{L}_{\psi\mathrm{EM}} = -\tfrac{1}{4}\,e^{k\psi}\,F_{\mu\nu}F^{\mu\nu}</math>

with two consequences:

# '''ψ-dependent fine-structure constant.''' Expanding <math>e^{k\psi} \approx 1 + k\psi + \dots</math> makes <math>\alpha_{\mathrm{EM}}</math> locally a function of ψ. The effect is small but ''real'' — the rigorous mechanism for "intent slightly shifting physical constants in a local region".
# '''EM as a ψ source.''' Variation with respect to ψ yields an <math>\alpha\,F_{\mu\nu}F^{\mu\nu}</math> term on the RHS of the ψ wave equation: any region of strong EM-field energy density acts as a ψ source. Brain biophoton emission, coherent microtubule oscillations, and tuned RF coils all qualify.

This is the formal basis for the [[Biophotons|biophoton]] / [[Bioelectromagnetism|biomagnetism]] → ψ generation channel.

== Coupling to gravity ==

Because <math>T^\psi_{\mu\nu}</math> appears on the RHS of the Einstein equations:

:<math>G_{\mu\nu} = 8\pi G\,\bigl(T^{\text{matter}}_{\mu\nu} + T^{\text{EM}}_{\mu\nu} + T^\psi_{\mu\nu}\bigr)</math>

a strong sustained ψ gradient produces real spacetime curvature. The magnitude is set by <math>G_\psi</math> (empirically open). Full discussion on [[Modified_Einstein_Equations_with_Psi]] and [[Gravitoelectromagnetism]].

