== Three field equations (legacy presentation) ==

The pre-merge ''Psi Field'' page presented three equations as a historically motivated entry into the formalism. They are special cases or rewrites of the full theory above.

=== Equation 1: ψ-energy flux (continuity with EM source/sink) ===

:<math>\partial_t\Psi + \nabla\!\cdot(\Psi\,\mathbf{v}) = -\alpha_E\,\nabla\!\cdot(\Psi\,\mathbf{E}) + \alpha_B\,\nabla\!\cdot(\Psi\,\mathbf{B}) + J^{\text{ext}}_\psi</math>

* Advective form of energy conservation with explicit ψ–EM exchange terms.
* <math>\alpha_E,\ \alpha_B</math> are dimensionless EM–ψ coupling constants.
* Physical basis: the <math>r = 0.95</math> correlation between biophoton emission and EEG power (Dotta et al. 2012), and the pharmacological causation of brain UPE by neural depolarisation (Tang & Dai 2014).

=== Equation 2: ψ stress-energy tensor ===

Already given above:

:<math>\mathcal{L}_\psi = \tfrac{1}{2}\,\partial^\mu\psi\,\partial_\mu\psi - \tfrac{1}{2} m^2\psi^2 - \tfrac{\lambda}{4}\psi^4</math>

:<math>T^\psi_{\mu\nu} = \partial_\mu\psi\,\partial_\nu\psi - g_{\mu\nu}\,\mathcal{L}_\psi</math>

with <math>T^{00} = \Psi</math>. Source: standard Klein–Gordon field theory.

=== Equation 3: ψ-field diffusion-reaction interaction ===

:<math>\nabla\!\cdot(\Psi\,\mathbf{E}) - \nabla\!\cdot(\Psi\,\mathbf{B}) = -\partial_t\Psi + \nabla^2\Psi</math>

* The <math>\mathbf{E}</math> and <math>\mathbf{B}</math> couplings represent the electromagnetic field components of biophoton emission from neural tissue.
* Empirical basis: brain biophoton ↔ EEG correlation (Dotta et al. 2012), neural-depolarisation causation (Tang & Dai 2014), myelinated-axon photonic-waveguide behaviour (Zarkeshian et al. 2018).

Together Eq. 1 governs advective transport with EM source/sink; Eq. 3 governs diffusive spatial coupling. They are not independent fundamentals; they are special-case descriptions of the full Lagrangian theory above.

== Scientific Foundations ==

The ψ-field framework is grounded in peer-reviewed research across multiple disciplines. Full review on [[Scientific_Foundations_of_Psionics]].

* '''Biophotonics:''' All living organisms emit ultra-weak photons (UPE) from mitochondrial ROS reactions (Mould et al. 2024 review; Popp lineage from 1976).
* '''Neural optics:''' Myelinated axons function as photonic waveguides (Zarkeshian et al. 2018).
* '''Microtubule quantum biology:''' Multi-band conductance resonances at kHz–MHz–GHz (Bandyopadhyay et al. 2014); superradiant excitonic states (Celardo et al. 2019); anaesthetic coupling (Kalra et al. 2023).
* '''Biomagnetism:''' Brain magnetic fields ~100 fT routinely measured by clinical SQUID-MEG and wearable OPM systems (Roth 2023; Rea et al. 2021; Bok et al. 2024).
* '''Anomalous cognition:''' Bem & Honorton 1994 ''Psychological Bulletin'' meta-analysis (ganzfeld); Mossbridge et al. 2012 ''Frontiers in Psychology'' meta-analysis (presentiment); Utts 1995 SRI/AIR review (remote viewing).

== Relationship with consciousness ==

ψ never has a "consciousness" variable bolted on. Consciousness enters only through:

* '''Coherent neural firing patterns''' shaping J<sub>ψ</sub> and the α F<sup>2</sup> source term.
* '''Focused attention''' sustaining large-amplitude, long-coherence-time ψ solitons via the λψ<sup>3</sup> nonlinearity.
* '''Neural ↔ ψ feedback''' encoded in [[Wilson-Cowan_Coupled_to_Psi|the Wilson–Cowan equation with β·ψ drive]].

